314
00:20:09,461 --> 00:20:14,760
I saw something shining when you showed us this film

315
00:20:14,761 --> 00:20:17,561
on the editor this afternoon.

316
00:20:21,161 --> 00:20:24,160
Just before the words "The End" appear onscreen,

317
00:20:24,161 --> 00:20:28,060
when Nagisa disappears from the shot...

318
00:20:28,061 --> 00:20:30,460
Right here.

319
00:20:30,461 --> 00:20:35,360
Can't you see something shining through the lace curtains?

320
00:20:35,361 --> 00:20:37,360
I see. You're right.

321
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:39,260
How embarrassing.

322
00:20:39,261 --> 00:20:43,260
I hadn't noticed in 40 years.

323
00:20:43,261 --> 00:20:46,660
That proves Dr. Agasa's story.

324
00:20:46,661 --> 00:20:50,461
Yes. Now, I can report the results to my mother.

325
00:20:51,861 --> 00:20:54,260
But I wonder what it was.

326
00:20:54,261 --> 00:20:56,360
-Could it be a star? -No.

327
00:20:56,361 --> 00:21:00,360
It was cloudy that day. There wasn't a single star in the sky.

328
00:21:00,361 --> 00:21:03,160
Then was it plane lights?

329
00:21:03,161 --> 00:21:05,160
A plane?

330
00:21:05,161 --> 00:21:07,560
I see. This is...

331
00:21:07,561 --> 00:21:11,260
That's right. This light was probably

332
00:21:11,261 --> 00:21:17,461
the now demolished Beika City aerial lighthouse.

